Company Overview of Lord Abbett Affiliated Fund, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Lord Abbett Affiliated Fund, Inc. is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Lord, Abbett & Co. LLC. It invests in the public equity markets of the United States. The fund seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in dividend-paying value stocks of large-cap companies within the market capitalization range of the Russell 1000 Index. The fund employs a combination of fundamental and quantitative analysis focusing on factors like company’s financial condition, long-term normalized earnings, earnings growth rates, changes in economic and financial environment, new or improved products or services, changes in management or structure ...
Lord Abbett Affiliated Fund, Inc. is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Lord, Abbett & Co. LLC. It invests in the public equity markets of the United States. The fund seeks to invest in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in dividend-paying value stocks of large-cap companies within the market capitalization range of the Russell 1000 Index. The fund employs a combination of fundamental and quantitative analysis focusing on factors like company’s financial condition, long-term normalized earnings, earnings growth rates, changes in economic and financial environment, new or improved products or services, changes in management or structure of the company, price increases for the company’s products or services, improved efficiencies, valuation, and risk models to create its portfolio. It benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the Russell 1000 Value Index and Lipper Equity Income funds Average. The fund employs proprietary research to create its portfolio. Lord Abbett Affiliated Fund, Inc. was formed on May 14, 1934 and is domiciled in the United States.
